senses.sense_text:
A location first mentioned at Gen.12.10; 
referred to as Egypt or Egyptian (מִצְרַ֫יִם), or Egypt (מָצוֹר), or Egypt (KJV, NIV= "rebellion") (מְרִי), or Rahab (רַ֫הַב), or Egyptian or Egypt or Egyptian women or "they" (KJV= Egyptians) (מִצְרִי), or Ham (חָם), or Egypt (Αἴγυπτος), or Egyptian (Αἰγύπτιος). §Meri, a name for Egypt 
This name means rebellion, rebellious
